description.narrative: (Georgia): The purpose of the New Economic Opportunities (NEO) initiative is to improve rural incomes, reduce poverty levels, improve food security, and address critical, small-scale infrastructure constraints in over 80 communities across Georgia. To achieve these goals, NEO supports community level economic development planning, rural economic development, income-generating activities for highly vulnerable groups, and interventions that enable internally displaced persons (IDP) to sustainably maintain their households. With FY 2014 funds, NEO will continue assisting 55 communities along the administrative boundary line (ABL) with South Ossetia, and further expand its small-scale infrastructure and income generating activities along the ABL. Specifically, NEO will implement 20 small-scale infrastructure activities (e.g., potable water systems, irrigation channels, drainage, tertiary roads) benefiting up to 4,000 households; deliver vocational training, interest free and/or low interest micro loans and trade-specific toolkits; and support the development of beekeeping, fruit/vegetable production, apparel-making, hairdressing, and a variety of construction and agricultural practices, benefiting at least 2,000 households. Approximately $50,000 of FY 2014 resources will be used to develop functioning value chains with a special focus on benefiting vulnerable populations.
